    {
      "step_id": "78492ad8",
      "step_index": 6,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "- **Structural alerts relevant to CYP2D6 inhibition:**  \n  - Many known CYP2D6 inhibitors have a **protonatable tertiary amine** (high pKa) that ion-pairs with Asp301 in CYP2D6.  \n  - Here, nitrogens are **amide/hydrazide and heteroaromatic**; these are typically **weakly basic to non-basic** (amide N essentially non-basic; heteroaromatic N often weak base). No clear **strongly protonatable tertiary amine**.",
