    {
      "step_id": "d8e1156f",
      "step_index": 8,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "**Features increasing likelihood of inhibition (general CYP binding):**\n- **Two phenyl rings + CF3** \u2192 high hydrophobic/aromatic surface that can sit in the CYP active site and promote tight binding.\n- Multiple **H-bond acceptors** (ring nitrogens, carbonyl) can help orient the ligand.",
      "tool_name": null,
